observations.recommendation:
We recommended that:

The financial reports, assessment data should be used as basis by the governing board of CDLN in its decision in devising measure to achieve the objective of self-sufficiency and effectiveness.  Likewise, the limitations of operating a LEE should be taken into consideration, bearing in mind the LGUs developmental goal, objectives and services that can be effectively discharge out of the funds extended to the LEE to continue operation;

Adopt cost-cutting measures to lessen expenditures and devise mechanism to boost revenue;

Revisit the ordinances and charter and ensure that no provisions therein are contrary to rules and regulations particularly RA 7160 and the Manual on the Setting Up and Operation of Local Economic Enterprises.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive:

Require the Municipal Engineer to inspect the water system, identify and evaluate any defects to appropriately recommend appropriate measure to maximize the use of this infrastructure;

Ensure that the necessary permit to construct the birthing facility is granted before pursuing the rehabilitation/ repair to avoid additional wastage of government funds;

Require the Municipal Engineer and the Municipal Treasurer to furnish the Municipal Accountant-designate all the records and documents relative to the construction and any rehabilitation on these infrastructure to facilitate the adjustment of the valuation and proper accounting recognition of the assets.
